PART 4: Production Troublshooting

1. Website is down. How to troubleshoot?
A: Step 1: check availability: is dns working? is alb working?
   Step 2: Check lb target groups are healthy, alb status, listner configuration
   Step 3: check ec2: uptime, top, df -h
   Step 4: check nginx : systemctl status nginx
   Step 5: check logs, container: docker ps, docker logs <container-id>, curl localhost:5000, tail -f /var/logs/nginx/error.log
   Step 6: check recent changes: new deployment? congif changes? sg changes?

2. You are getting 502 bad gateway error. how?
A: 502 error means that proxy server cannot communicate with the backend application
   Resolve: check if docker container stopped: docker ps -a (if it shows exited means its stopped)
            if exited then start the container : docker start container-id
            check application logs: docker logs container-id
            check flask port: netstat -tulpn
            test backend: curl localhost:5000 --> if it fails then flask issue, if it passes then nginx issue

3. You are getting 503 service unavailable error. how?
A: 503 error means load balancer has no healthy targets 
    check if target group is healthy
    login to ec2 and check docker ps, systemctl status nginx 
    check sg and see that port is allowed

4. docker container keeps restarting
A: First i will check y the container is crashing
   check status: docker ps -a
   check logs: docker logs <container-id>
   check exit code: docker inspect <container-id>
  Common issues: dependency issue, port conflict, memory issue, missing env variables

5. Docker image size is 5gb, how to reduce it?
A: --> choose a smaller base image: instead of python:latest use python:3.11-slim
   --> multi stage build: build dependencies seperately
   --> remove un-necessary files , use : .dockerignore : ex: .git, _pycache_
   --> combine run commands

6. ec2 disk usage reaches 100%.
A: df -h
   du -sh * to find large files
   check logs: /var/log
   docker usage: docker system df
   cleanup : docker system prune
   long term solution: increase ebs volume, send logs to cloud watch, configure log rotation

7. ec2 memory reaches 95%
A: check : free -m
   check processes: top or htop
   check the most memory consuming process
   solution: restart the application, increase instance size, add asg

8. application is slow suddenly, what to check?
A: check cloud watch for cpu, memory, disk, network
   check lb: target health, response time, request count
   check application logs
   db : check query performance
   traffic: check sudden traffic increase or no

