11. How do you handle failed deployments?
A: i use rollback strategies
    Options: Blue green deployment: Old version: A, New Version : B, switch traffic after validation
             Canary: releases small percentage of new application: 5% users new application, 95% users old application. It monitors this, then does complete rollout.

12. Why move ec2+ docker to k8s?
A: Docker is for packaging the application, but k8s is for managing the containers at scale.
   k8s provides: container orchestration, load balancing, scaling, auto healing, rolling updates, service discovery

13. How do you migrate this project to k8s?
A: current: ec2, docker container, flask
   conversion to k8s: convert to eks cluster --> deployment --> pods --> service --> ingress --> users

14. Explain k8s architecture
A: Control plane ( master node): API server, scheduler, controller manager, etcd
   worker node: kubelet, container runtime, pods

